com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util

Class Bindings

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util.Bindings

  • public class Bindings
extends java.lang.Object
    A Bindings declares the Bindings of a special kind of PropagatorFunction, the PropagatorFunctionBindings and is provided by PropagatorFunctionBindings#doGetBindings().

    A Bindings provides a collection of Bindings.InboundBindings and collection of Bindings.OutboundBinding.

    An inbound Bindings decides when a modication is binding by implementing the method Bindings.InboundBinding.notifyChanged(PropagatorFunctionSource, Notification), that must call PropagatorFunctionSource.touch(EObject) when there is inbound binding.

    An outbound Bindings decides when an adapter is setting an element by implementing the method Bindings.OutboundBinding.isOutboundBinding(PropagatorFunctionSource, Object), that must return true when there is outbound binding.

    Author:
    michel

      • isTrackToucher

        protected boolean isTrackToucher
        When the dependency is 'TrackToucher' - the Notifier(s) touching - the toucher(s) - will be passed to the calculate method. When more than one toucher is involved, the calculate method is invoked for every toucher.
